			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just as the first reply on the post by Brad, I must say thats an interesting point of view, well said and thoughtout.  I would just like to take the chance to say that the reason EQ players complain so much, is out of the fact that they can truly change the game.  Verant listens, and sometimes I wonder how they get any work done with how actively they listen to their audience.  In no other game have I seen such a level of involvement, passion, and care by the development team, players, etc.<BR>
<BR>
But the main reason I am writing this message is cause so few realize what a golden age we are in with MMORPG's (yes, its in its infancy, but thats not the point), ten years from now when EQ has steped back and bowed down to Verants latest creation (or two), many will look back and say wow, that was some fun.  And truly it is, it parallels being a kid and growing up, only to find out when you finally get a job how great kindergarden really was, wishing we had enjoyed it and APPERCIATED it for all its worth.  <BR>
<BR>
With this post, just as Brads, I hope that some of you will look at the game and start to experience it.  I know I'm not going to miss my kindergarden trip though MMORPG's, and I hope you won't either.<BR>
<BR>
-Chartarus<BR>

