Nice comments and stuff. ;)<BR>
Most of the things I've seen in my limited time playing EQ haven't been that bad in the since I don't get up in disgust (Well, except Highhold... I hate that place).<BR>
Most of the issues with EQ are just strictly ironing out game balance and mechanics which, I'm afraid to say, will always be ongoing.<BR>
EQ for me fills the gap left by not being able to play table top RPGs with any frequency. I am hoping that EQ in the long run will be the boost table top RPGs need to survive. RPGs for the masses as it were. We'll see.<BR>
<BR>
All I ask is to treat it more like a RPG not a computer game. Start looking for things that promote actual role playing instead of roll playing.<BR>
<BR>
